WEBVTT

00:10.503 --> 00:14.138
¶ ¶

00:19.579 --> 00:22.046
(bell rings)

00:23.783 --> 00:26.517
How may I he...?

00:27.787 --> 00:29.354
Devil's night.

00:29.356 --> 00:31.422
I have a standing reservation.

00:31.424 --> 00:33.925
Of course, Mr. Ramirez.

00:33.927 --> 00:37.028
Well, my pleasure to welcome you
to the Hotel Cortez.

00:37.030 --> 00:38.629
Uh, this is your
second year joining us?

00:38.631 --> 00:39.630
Third.

00:39.632 --> 00:41.666
I died in 2013.

00:41.668 --> 00:43.334
(laughs):
Apologies.

00:43.336 --> 00:45.103
Let me show you
to your room.

00:45.105 --> 00:47.171
(elevator bell dings)
RAMIREZ: I was hoping Manson
could join us this year.

00:47.173 --> 00:50.608
LIZ:
Charlie hasn't shuffled
off this mortal coil yet.

00:50.610 --> 00:53.378
He's still serving
life in State prison.

00:53.380 --> 00:54.879
Aw, that's too bad.

00:54.881 --> 00:56.481
Your room, sir.

00:56.483 --> 00:59.650
The master has left
a couple of treats

00:59.652 --> 01:02.020
on the pillow.

01:02.022 --> 01:03.254
I don't need a key.

01:24.044 --> 01:26.377
¶ ¶

01:47.033 --> 01:48.499
(grunts)

01:50.070 --> 01:52.103
(screams)
(shushes)

01:52.105 --> 01:54.038
Shut up!

01:54.040 --> 01:55.440
Swear to Satan you won't scream

01:55.442 --> 01:58.109
or I'll kill you.

01:58.111 --> 01:59.277
(muffled grunts)

01:59.279 --> 02:00.945
I said swear to Satan!

02:00.947 --> 02:04.282
I swear to Satan.

02:04.284 --> 02:06.117
(screaming)

02:06.119 --> 02:08.086
You liar!

02:10.723 --> 02:12.290
No! (coughing)

02:12.292 --> 02:14.258
(mumbling)

02:15.562 --> 02:16.794
(crackling)

02:18.865 --> 02:20.698
Help! Help me!

02:20.700 --> 02:24.035
There's a killer after me!

02:24.037 --> 02:25.369
And a killer before you.

02:26.773 --> 02:29.073
Ricky!

02:29.075 --> 02:31.142
Found your presents.

02:31.144 --> 02:32.743
Tourists from Arizona.

02:32.745 --> 02:34.712
Marriot was full.

02:34.714 --> 02:37.815
Come, finish her off.
(whimpers)

03:49.822 --> 03:52.256
(phone ringing)

03:59.966 --> 04:01.199
Hello?

04:01.201 --> 04:02.400
Hey, Dad.

04:02.402 --> 04:03.734
Hey, sweetie.

04:03.736 --> 04:06.270
Hey.

04:09.042 --> 04:11.242
How was Disneyland?

04:11.244 --> 04:13.244
It's pretty cool.

04:13.246 --> 04:15.246
I was just on my way out.

04:15.248 --> 04:16.881
Uh, I'll be over at Grandma's
in about an hour.

04:16.883 --> 04:20.218
We've got some
Halloween shopping to do.

04:20.220 --> 04:22.386
I don't really feel like

04:22.388 --> 04:24.055
going trick-or-treating
this year.

04:24.057 --> 04:26.057
Oh, um, okay.

04:26.059 --> 04:28.259
We can do something else.

04:28.261 --> 04:29.193
Actually,

04:29.195 --> 04:30.428
Grandma was gonna teach me

04:30.430 --> 04:32.063
how to make banana cream pie.

04:32.065 --> 04:33.864
Kind of takes a while.

04:33.866 --> 04:35.766
Oh, you want to stay
over there for a lit...

04:35.768 --> 04:36.867
a little while longer?

04:36.869 --> 04:38.169
If that's okay.

04:38.171 --> 04:40.104
Look, things are a little bit...

04:40.106 --> 04:41.672
(bubbling nearby)

04:41.674 --> 04:45.009
...weird right now, aren't they?

04:45.011 --> 04:47.411
A little bit.

04:47.413 --> 04:49.447
I got to go.

04:49.449 --> 04:51.449
Bye, Dad.

04:51.451 --> 04:53.050
Bye, Scar.

04:53.052 --> 04:55.319
I love you.

05:07.467 --> 05:10.101
(blood dripping rapidly)

05:22.248 --> 05:23.948
(gasps)

05:32.292 --> 05:35.826
BOY:
<i> I don't like my costume.</i>

05:44.270 --> 05:46.904
Come along, Albert.

05:51.244 --> 05:53.678
Here, put this on.

05:53.680 --> 05:55.279
I don't like my costume.

05:55.281 --> 05:58.516
Nothing's good enough
for you, Mr. Bellyache.

06:00.653 --> 06:02.286
There are places
in the country where they

06:02.288 --> 06:03.521
put paper bags over
the children's head

06:03.523 --> 06:05.089
and call that a costume.

06:05.091 --> 06:07.325
Shake a leg.

06:07.327 --> 06:09.527
I like to be punctual.

06:09.529 --> 06:11.429
(laughing):
Well...

06:11.431 --> 06:13.364
look at you, Molly Wilkins!

06:13.366 --> 06:16.267
You must've been
sewing for months!

06:16.269 --> 06:19.603
Pulled out all the stops, didn't
you, with that expensive lace?

06:19.605 --> 06:23.541
Oh, goodness, I wish I'd had
time to sew a proper pattern...

06:23.543 --> 06:24.809
Boo!

06:24.811 --> 06:26.310
You're a scary little ghost.

06:26.312 --> 06:27.545
MS. EVERS
...do things with your time,

06:27.547 --> 06:28.979
while I'm taking
in the laundry

06:28.981 --> 06:30.481
and mending clothes.

06:30.483 --> 06:31.716
But I'm so envious.

06:31.718 --> 06:33.317
You look so lovely.

06:33.319 --> 06:35.353
I do feel bad for little Albert.

06:35.355 --> 06:37.355
He wanted
an African cheetah costume,

06:37.357 --> 06:41.192
but I just never
found the time.

06:41.194 --> 06:44.895
Where is he,
the little rascal?

06:44.897 --> 06:47.431
(car engine starts up)

06:48.568 --> 06:50.601
No! Please stop!

06:55.141 --> 06:56.140
(knocking)

06:56.142 --> 06:57.575
Who is it?

06:57.577 --> 06:59.977
It's John Lowe from downstairs.

06:59.979 --> 07:00.911
Oh!

07:04.183 --> 07:06.050
I'm busy!

07:08.254 --> 07:10.321
I'm working on these sheets!

07:17.730 --> 07:19.230
What happened here?
Was there an accident?

07:19.232 --> 07:20.664
It happens every year.

07:20.666 --> 07:22.666
At this time.

07:22.668 --> 07:24.535
I-I lost my boy on Halloween.

07:24.537 --> 07:28.372
So every year I go a little mad
and I make a mess of everything.

07:28.374 --> 07:31.409
And I can't get a-a handle
on the sheet situation.

07:31.411 --> 07:33.444
You lost your boy?

07:33.446 --> 07:34.845
You mean he died?

07:34.847 --> 07:36.847
Not right away.

07:36.849 --> 07:38.015
How did you lose him?

07:38.017 --> 07:40.251
I didn't see!

07:40.253 --> 07:42.353
I wasn't paying attention!

07:44.023 --> 07:46.257
(crying):
It was my fault!

07:46.259 --> 07:48.225
I should've made him
a proper costume,

07:48.227 --> 07:50.361
like all the children.

07:50.363 --> 07:52.463
I know how that feels,

07:52.465 --> 07:55.366
especially
around the anniversary.

07:55.368 --> 07:58.269
I-I made him wear
a plain old sheet.

07:58.271 --> 08:00.404
Just a plain old sheet.

08:00.406 --> 08:04.442
Why didn't I pay
more attention?!

08:04.444 --> 08:05.576
I'm not really sure.

08:05.578 --> 08:07.044
I feel like I'm living

08:07.046 --> 08:09.547
in a walking nightmare.

08:14.420 --> 08:16.487
Would you like a sherry?

08:20.293 --> 08:21.559
I'm okay, thank you.

08:21.561 --> 08:23.828
I'll let you
get back...

08:23.830 --> 08:25.996
Will-will you pour me one?

08:28.267 --> 08:29.433
Talking with you

08:29.435 --> 08:32.002
is a comfort to my soul.

08:45.351 --> 08:49.286
They searched the
city for days.

08:49.288 --> 08:52.156
But he wasn't
in the city.

08:52.158 --> 08:55.593
<i> His killer...</i>
<i> took him to his ranch</i>

08:55.595 --> 08:57.461
<i> up in Wineville.</i>

08:57.463 --> 08:59.029
(chickens clucking)

09:04.604 --> 09:07.338
<i> Oh, God, help me!</i>

09:09.842 --> 09:12.476
<i> He haunts my dreams.</i>

09:12.478 --> 09:15.980
<i> His woeful eyes pierce me</i>
<i> with accusations.</i>

09:15.982 --> 09:19.416
Why weren't you careful Mommy?

09:21.721 --> 09:23.287
Didn't you love me, Mommy?

09:23.289 --> 09:26.190
(crying)

09:26.192 --> 09:29.260
Of course I loved him!

09:34.133 --> 09:36.400
At least you know
what happened to your boy.

09:39.705 --> 09:41.205
But I don't.

09:41.207 --> 09:42.606
Not really.

09:57.490 --> 10:01.158
This is all we found
of your boy, ma'am.

10:01.160 --> 10:03.027
That sicko disposed

10:03.029 --> 10:05.763
of all their bodies
in quicklime.

10:05.765 --> 10:07.565
And then he scattered
their bones in a mass grave.

10:07.567 --> 10:11.435
Oh...

10:11.437 --> 10:13.304
(screams)

10:16.409 --> 10:18.409
They never were sure exactly

10:18.411 --> 10:20.578
how many children there were.

10:20.580 --> 10:24.548
That is a terrible story, Ms...

10:24.550 --> 10:26.750
Evers.

10:26.752 --> 10:29.186
Hazel Evers.

10:29.188 --> 10:31.555
You can call me Hazel.

10:31.557 --> 10:33.023
I'm John.

10:33.025 --> 10:36.794
I know.

10:36.796 --> 10:39.597
I have a confession
to make, John.

10:39.599 --> 10:43.133
I've known for a while
that we were kindred spirits.

10:43.135 --> 10:45.769
(laughing)

10:45.771 --> 10:47.972
Oh, my!

10:47.974 --> 10:49.773
Oh, my, it's so late
and I'm so behind!

10:49.775 --> 10:52.042
There's so much to do
before the shindig tonight,

10:52.044 --> 10:53.143
and so little time!

10:53.145 --> 10:54.745
The master will be

10:54.747 --> 10:57.548
very very upset if his
table isn't perfect.

10:57.550 --> 11:00.217
His autumnal banquet
is the event of the year.

11:00.219 --> 11:03.087
These particular guests,
they're very demanding.

11:03.089 --> 11:05.756
Refills, refills, refills!

11:05.758 --> 11:07.625
My feet are swollen up
like puff pastries

11:07.627 --> 11:09.059
by the end of the night!

11:28.681 --> 11:30.714
(barking)

11:31.817 --> 11:35.019
Jasper, stop that.

11:35.021 --> 11:36.186
Come here, come here.

11:36.188 --> 11:37.588
Jasper, come on.

11:38.691 --> 11:40.124
In here.

11:40.126 --> 11:43.494
(Jasper growls)

11:43.496 --> 11:46.764
He's a sweet dog.

11:46.766 --> 11:48.265
He just doesn't
know who you are.

11:48.267 --> 11:49.833
We got him two years ago.

11:49.835 --> 11:51.702
Your sister was lonely.

11:56.108 --> 11:57.808
I'm gonna do an exam.

11:57.810 --> 11:59.743
It'll only take a minute, okay?

12:01.113 --> 12:03.280
It's too bright.

12:03.282 --> 12:04.615
Sorry.

12:06.018 --> 12:08.185
I'm sorry.
Come over here, baby.

12:12.658 --> 12:15.526
Can you sit
still for me?

12:18.130 --> 12:19.430
(thermometer beeps)

12:21.634 --> 12:24.568
Do you feel cold?

12:24.570 --> 12:26.136
No.

12:26.138 --> 12:28.505
No?

12:28.507 --> 12:30.774
Do you know where
you are, baby?

12:32.878 --> 12:35.312
Hmm? Do you remember
this house?

12:37.717 --> 12:39.917
You're home.

12:39.919 --> 12:42.953
You're finally home, baby.

12:44.356 --> 12:46.423
Oh, I've missed you
so much.

12:48.694 --> 12:51.795
I'm thirsty.

12:52.765 --> 12:54.832
Of course you are.

12:54.834 --> 12:56.900
I'll get you some juice,
all right?

12:58.571 --> 13:00.904
Be right back.

13:17.790 --> 13:18.956
(sobs quietly)

13:21.727 --> 13:23.994
(sobbing)

13:41.881 --> 13:43.013
(sniffs)

13:53.759 --> 13:55.759
Holden, I've brought you
an apple juice

13:55.761 --> 13:57.227
and an orange juice.

13:57.229 --> 13:58.862
Wasn't sure which one...

13:59.799 --> 14:01.198
Holden?

14:04.170 --> 14:07.070
Holden!
(Jasper whimpers)

14:07.072 --> 14:09.072
What is wrong
with you?

14:09.074 --> 14:10.908
I don't feel good.

14:11.610 --> 14:13.076
I need my mommy.

14:13.078 --> 14:14.912
Baby, I am your mommy.

14:14.914 --> 14:16.747
My other mommy.

14:22.421 --> 14:24.688
It's confirmed.

14:24.690 --> 14:27.191
Blood on your junkie
wasn't his.

14:27.193 --> 14:29.159
So we're looking for a body now.

14:29.161 --> 14:31.929
You don't think
we have enough bodies?

14:33.632 --> 14:35.199
Hey, how come
I've never heard of a town

14:35.201 --> 14:36.633
where 20 kiddie murders

14:36.635 --> 14:38.268
and abductions
supposedly took place?

14:38.270 --> 14:40.804
Are you talking about the
Wineville Chicken Coop Murders?

14:40.806 --> 14:42.639
They changed the name
of the town.

14:42.641 --> 14:44.708
Bad publicity.

14:44.710 --> 14:46.476
When?

14:46.478 --> 14:48.078
Hell, 60 years ago?

14:51.851 --> 14:53.784
Eighty-five.

14:55.988 --> 14:58.188
85... years...

14:58.190 --> 15:00.858
The crimes took place
in the '20s?

15:00.860 --> 15:03.527
Does this have something to do
with our Bible-thumper?

15:03.529 --> 15:04.628
I don't know.

15:04.630 --> 15:06.897
HAHN:
John?

15:06.899 --> 15:08.799
John, you okay?

15:37.730 --> 15:39.796
¶ ¶

16:07.893 --> 16:10.894
COUNTESS:
You must have
a lot of questions.

16:10.896 --> 16:14.164
I have answers.

16:25.377 --> 16:27.044
It must have been
a shock for you

16:27.046 --> 16:28.278
to see your boy.

16:28.280 --> 16:29.546
I imagined you'd
lost hope long ago.

16:29.548 --> 16:30.981
I never gave up.

16:30.983 --> 16:32.316
No, you didn't.

16:32.318 --> 16:33.784
Your devotion moved me.

16:33.786 --> 16:36.553
I could feel your longing.

16:37.823 --> 16:38.956
Holden felt it, too.

16:38.958 --> 16:40.357
That's why
he came to you.

16:41.994 --> 16:43.994
You stole my son.

16:43.996 --> 16:46.096
I saved him.

16:46.098 --> 16:47.731
Like I save all my children.

16:47.733 --> 16:50.701
From what?

16:52.905 --> 16:54.938
Neglect.

16:54.940 --> 16:56.506
I could see
where they were headed.

16:56.508 --> 16:58.241
A tragic, wasted life.

16:58.243 --> 16:59.776
I opened my heart

16:59.778 --> 17:00.944
and the children
came to me willingly.

17:00.946 --> 17:02.779
I never neglected my son.

17:02.781 --> 17:05.182
Can you say the same
about your husband?

17:06.151 --> 17:08.018
Here you go.

17:09.989 --> 17:12.055
(phone buzzing)

17:16.929 --> 17:18.595
Yeah.

17:18.597 --> 17:20.097
Yeah, I'll meet you
at the station later.

17:27.673 --> 17:30.007
JOHN:
Holden!

17:30.009 --> 17:33.110
(carnival music playing)

17:33.112 --> 17:34.845
Holden?!

17:36.982 --> 17:38.215
<i> Holden!</i>

17:42.021 --> 17:45.489
I brought them here
to keep them safe.

17:45.491 --> 17:48.025
The world can be
such a dangerous place.

17:48.027 --> 17:50.827
I've had enough
of your bullshit.

17:50.829 --> 17:53.063
What did you do to my son?

17:53.065 --> 17:54.464
You're a doctor.

17:54.466 --> 17:56.133
I'm going to put it to you

17:56.135 --> 17:58.902
in a way that
you can understand.

17:58.904 --> 18:01.171
Holden has contracted
an ancient virus.

18:01.173 --> 18:03.040
A blood disorder.

18:03.042 --> 18:05.308
The effect of the disease
is health,

18:05.310 --> 18:07.644
vitality and everlasting life.

18:12.084 --> 18:15.085
Whatever you did to him...

18:15.087 --> 18:17.320
...change him back.
Is this why you came up here?

18:17.322 --> 18:19.056
Change him back
or I'll kill you.

18:19.058 --> 18:21.091
There is no going back.

18:21.093 --> 18:22.726
No.

18:22.728 --> 18:25.262
I'm his mother.

18:25.264 --> 18:27.030
We'll find a cure.

18:27.032 --> 18:28.732
There is no cure.

18:28.734 --> 18:30.901
The only way you can truly be
with Holden is to join him.

18:30.903 --> 18:33.837
Alex, I'm offering you eternity

18:33.839 --> 18:35.605
with your great lost love.

18:35.607 --> 18:38.008
What I wouldn't trade
for a chance at that.

18:38.010 --> 18:41.945
And what are you asking me
to trade for it?

18:41.947 --> 18:44.014
What's the price I have to pay
to be like you?

18:44.016 --> 18:46.550
Your undying loyalty.

18:46.552 --> 18:48.151
You'll be working for me.

18:50.222 --> 18:52.189
Here.

18:53.892 --> 18:56.159
Take this. It will
calm your nerves.

18:58.197 --> 19:00.263
You're insane.

19:00.265 --> 19:01.765
You're going down.

19:01.767 --> 19:03.934
I'm getting the police.

19:03.936 --> 19:04.935
(screams)

19:06.738 --> 19:08.105
(whimpers)

19:08.107 --> 19:09.206
Let her go.

19:17.382 --> 19:19.583
She said she's gonna
go to the cops.

19:19.585 --> 19:21.318
She won't.

19:21.320 --> 19:25.055
She would never risk
losing her one true love.

19:25.057 --> 19:27.891
Wait, you're
banging her, too?

19:27.893 --> 19:29.960
¶ ¶

19:52.818 --> 19:55.252
What'll it be, soldier?

19:56.989 --> 19:59.789
Ginger ale?

19:59.791 --> 20:02.559
Shirley Temple?

20:12.638 --> 20:15.705
My soon to be ex-wife

20:15.707 --> 20:17.607
says I was never an alcoholic.

20:19.545 --> 20:23.013
According to her,
I'm just a control freak.

20:27.452 --> 20:30.086
I'll have a double martini.

20:33.959 --> 20:35.792
That's my boy.

20:35.794 --> 20:39.563
Control...
is an illusion.

20:39.565 --> 20:41.965
JOHN:
Tonight I surrender
to the illusion.

20:41.967 --> 20:43.300
(cocktail shaker rattles)

20:46.205 --> 20:48.405
(rock music playing)

20:59.551 --> 21:01.751
WOMAN:
Hey, sailor.

21:04.223 --> 21:05.355
Didn't see you come in.

21:05.357 --> 21:08.692
I will stand on my head
in a skirt

21:08.694 --> 21:10.260
for a ciggy and a beer.

21:10.262 --> 21:12.829
No need for
acrobatics.

21:12.831 --> 21:14.231
Drinks are
on me tonight.

21:14.233 --> 21:16.199
LIZ:
Now, Aileen,

21:16.201 --> 21:19.102
you be nice to Mr. Lowe.

21:19.705 --> 21:21.671
This is, what,

21:21.673 --> 21:24.107
your tenth year with us
at the hotel?

21:24.109 --> 21:26.409
Lucky 13th!
LIZ:
Ooh!

21:26.411 --> 21:28.345
Since 2002.

21:38.724 --> 21:40.624
Do I know you?

21:40.626 --> 21:43.059
I don't know.

21:43.061 --> 21:46.863
You ever picked up a hooker
along I-95 in Florida?

21:48.300 --> 21:50.900
No, I think I'd remember that.

21:50.902 --> 21:53.203
John...

21:53.205 --> 21:57.440
is a police officer...

21:57.442 --> 21:59.809
and a special guest

21:59.811 --> 22:02.345
of the hotel.

22:05.484 --> 22:07.617
Cop.

22:07.619 --> 22:09.753
A cop.

22:09.755 --> 22:11.254
(laughs)

22:11.256 --> 22:12.922
Man! Man.

22:12.924 --> 22:15.325
(bottle clunks on bar)

22:15.327 --> 22:17.460
Man, are you lucky
that I haven't had a beer

22:17.462 --> 22:20.330
in over a year,
or there is no way in hell

22:20.332 --> 22:21.931
I would let you
buy me one.

22:21.933 --> 22:23.333
They call me
a serial killer?

22:23.335 --> 22:27.370
Greatest serial killer
of all time is the cops.

22:29.141 --> 22:31.508
I know who you are.

22:31.510 --> 22:35.078
That is
an outstanding costume.

22:35.080 --> 22:37.480
Holy shit, you look
just like her.

22:37.482 --> 22:39.783
Her who?
Aileen Wuornos.

22:39.785 --> 22:41.117
Just saw a documentary
about her.

